 A man in his thirties has been arrested for allegedly raping and terrorising women in front of their children. He was charged
on eleven counts ranging from rape, sexual assault, kidnapping and robbery. The suspect
reportedly committed the crimes in Jozini earlier this month. The suspect
fled the area to Inanda where he was in hiding. Police
spokesperson Colonel Thembeka Mbele said he committed another case of assault
and he was arrested by Inanda police officers. “The
suspect terrorised women in Jozini by raping, kidnaping and robbing them of
their belongings,” Mbele said. In a
statement, Mbele said in one of the incidents, the suspect approached three
siblings who were at their homestead, Jozini where he threatened them. He
allegedly raped three of them in front of their children, the suspect further
took their cellphones, cash and clothing before he fled the scene. A case of
rape was opened at Jozini police station. 